cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the calibration performance of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of temperature scaling is a popular technique for calibration, which falls under the category of model post-processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of deep neural networks and augmentation techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of results, which could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
